Fix this Rust code:

```rust
fn main() {
    let s = String::from("hello");
    let t = s;
    println!("{}", s);
}
```

The value `s` is moved into `t`, so `s` cannot be used afterward. Clone it if both values are needed.

```rust
fn main() {
    let s = String::from("hello");
    let t = s.clone();
    println!("{}", s);
    println!("{}", t);
}
```

Fix this Rust code:

```rust
fn main() {
    let count = 0;
    count += 1;
    println!("{}", count);
}
```

The binding must be mutable before it can be changed.

```rust
fn main() {
    let mut count = 0;
    count += 1;
    println!("{}", count);
}
```
